data-triple-N3.o: "The Humboldt University of Berlin (German: Humboldt-Universitat zu Berlin) is one of Berlin's oldest universities, founded in 1810 as the University of Berlin (Universitat zu Berlin) by the liberal Prussian educational reformer and linguist Wilhelm von Humboldt, whose university model has strongly influenced other European and Western universities."@en
